# Object-Oriented Patterns in TwinCAT3

## Inheritance — EXTENDS

```iecst
// Base FB
FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_Base
VAR
    _bInitialized : BOOL;
END_VAR

METHOD Initialize : BOOL
    _bInitialized := TRUE;
    Initialize    := TRUE;
END_METHOD
```

```iecst
// Derived FB
FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_Derived EXTENDS FB_Base
VAR
    _fSpeed : REAL;
END_VAR

METHOD Initialize : BOOL
    SUPER^.Initialize(); // Call base method first
    _fSpeed := 0.0;
    Initialize := TRUE;
END_METHOD
```

Rules:
- `SUPER^.Method()` calls the parent implementation
- Derived FB has access to all public/protected members of base
- Can override any method — `SUPER^` is optional

## Interfaces

```iecst
// Interface definition (.TcPOU, SpecialFunc="None")
INTERFACE I_Controller
METHOD Start  : BOOL
METHOD Stop   : BOOL
METHOD IsRunning : BOOL
END_INTERFACE
```

```iecst
// FB implementing interface
FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_MotorController IMPLEMENTS I_Controller
METHOD Start : BOOL
    _bRunning := TRUE;
    Start     := TRUE;
END_METHOD

METHOD Stop : BOOL
    _bRunning := FALSE;
    Stop      := TRUE;
END_METHOD

METHOD IsRunning : BOOL
    IsRunning := _bRunning;
END_METHOD
```

```iecst
// Usage via interface reference
VAR
    iCtrl : I_Controller; // interface variable
END_VAR

// Assign concrete instance
iCtrl := fbMotorController;

// Call via interface
IF iCtrl.Start() THEN ...
```

## Abstract FBs

Cannot be instantiated directly. Use `ABSTRACT` keyword:

```iecst
{attribute 'hide'}
FUNCTION_BLOCK ABSTRACT FB_AbstractBase
VAR
    _bEnabled : BOOL;
END_VAR

METHOD ABSTRACT Process : BOOL  // must be implemented by derived FB
```

## Properties

Properties provide getter/setter access to private state. In .TcPOU XML, each property needs 3 GUIDs (Property + Get + Set).

```iecst
// Getter
PROPERTY IsEnabled : BOOL
// Get implementation:
IsEnabled := _bEnabled;

// Setter
// Set implementation:
_bEnabled := IsEnabled;
```

Call with dot notation:
```iecst
fbMotor.IsEnabled := TRUE;   // calls Set
bState := fbMotor.IsEnabled; // calls Get
```

Property names: PascalCase (no prefix). Mark read-only properties by omitting the `Set` accessor.

## FB_init — Dependency Injection

Use `FB_init` to inject references at instantiation time. Only called once when FB is created.

```iecst
{attribute 'hide'}
METHOD FB_init : BOOL
VAR_INPUT
    bInitRetains   : BOOL;
    bInCopyCode    : BOOL;
    fbComClient    : REFERENCE TO FB_SomeClient; // injected dependency
END_VAR
IF bInCopyCode THEN RETURN; END_IF

_fbComClient REF= fbComClient; // store reference
```

Rules:
- Always guard with `IF bInCopyCode THEN RETURN; END_IF`
- Use `REFERENCE TO` for non-nullable references; validate with `__ISVALIDREF(ref)` before use
- `FB_reinit` is called on warm reset; `FB_exit` before deletion

## Interface Variables

Store interface references in FB for polymorphism:

```iecst
VAR
    _ipBase : I_Controller; // interface pointer/reference
END_VAR

// Assign in FB_init:
_ipBase := THIS^; // self-assignment for delegation

// Call:
IF _ipBase <> 0 THEN
    _ipBase.Start();
END_IF
```

Use `<> 0` to check interface pointer validity (not `__ISVALIDREF`).
